By Aisha Cole Lagos – The Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) said it was expecting 30 ships to bring petroleum products, food and other goods from May 1to  May 15, at Apapa and Tin Can Island Ports. NPA made this known in its daily publication ‘Shipping Position’, adding that five of the 30 ships would sail in with petrol and one ship with diesel. The other 24 ships are carrying  general cargo, bulk malt, buthane, frozen fish, buckwheat , empty container and containers carrying different goods. According to the NPA, six ship have arrived the ports waiting to berth with frozen fish, contianers and petrol.